<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active throughout spring and summer, ranging in total length 7-10 mm and 1.5-3 mm in maximum width. Like the other species of this genus, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. l. subsp. longicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="subSpecies" species="l." subSpecies="longicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">A. l. longicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nocturnal and readily attracted to artificial lights. There is no published information on its larval host plant(s).
</paragraph>
